<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>JavaScript Learning Platform</title>
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.1.3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <link href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.0.0/css/all.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <link href="/css/style.css" rel="stylesheet">
</head>
<body>
    <nav class="navbar navbar-expand-lg navbar-dark bg-primary">
        <div class="container">
            <a class="navbar-brand" href="/">
                <i class="fas fa-code"></i> JavaScript Learning Platform
            </a>
            <button class="navbar-toggler" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#navbarNav">
                <span class="navbar-toggler-icon"></span>
            </button>
            <div class="collapse navbar-collapse" id="navbarNav">
                <ul class="navbar-nav ms-auto">
                    <li class="nav-item">
                        <a class="nav-link" href="/">Home</a>
                    </li>
                    <li class="nav-item">
                        <a class="nav-link" href="/api/modules">API</a>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </nav>

    <main class="container my-4">
        <div class="hero-section bg-primary text-white text-center py-5 mb-5 rounded">
            <h1 class="display-4"><i class="fas fa-graduation-cap"></i> JavaScript Learning Platform</h1>
            <p class="lead">Master JavaScript with our comprehensive 10-module course</p>
        </div>

        <div class="row">
            <% modules.forEach((module, index) => { %>
                <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-4 mb-4">
                    <div class="card h-100 shadow-sm module-card">
                        <div class="card-header bg-light">
                            <h5 class="card-title mb-0">
                                <span class="badge bg-primary me-2">Module <%= module.id %></span>
                                <%= module.title %>
                            </h5>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card-body">
                            <p class="card-text"><%= module.description %></p>
                            <div class="topics mb-3">
                                <h6>Topics Covered:</h6>
                                <ul class="list-unstyled">
                                    <% module.topics.forEach(topic => { %>
                                        <li><i class="fas fa-check text-success me-2"></i><%= topic %></li>
                                    <% }); %>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card-footer bg-white">
                            <div class="d-flex justify-content-between">
                                <a href="/module/<%= module.id %>" class="btn btn-primary">
                                    <i class="fas fa-eye"></i> View Details
                                </a>
                                <a href="/download/<%= module.id %>" class="btn btn-success">
                                    <i class="fas fa-download"></i> Download PDF
                                </a>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            <% }); %>
        </div>

        <div class="row mt-5">
            <div class="col-12">
                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-header">
                        <h3><i class="fas fa-info-circle"></i> About This Course</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-body">
                        <p>This comprehensive JavaScript course is designed to take you from beginner to advanced level. Each module builds upon the previous one, ensuring a smooth learning progression.</p>
                        <div class="row">
                            <div class="col-md-6">
                                <h5>What You'll Learn:</h5>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>JavaScript fundamentals and syntax</li>
                                    <li>Control structures and functions</li>
                                    <li>Object-oriented programming</li>
                                    <li>DOM manipulation and events</li>
                                    <li>Asynchronous programming</li>
                                    <li>Modern ES6+ features</li>
                                    <li>Error handling and debugging</li>
                                    <li>Testing methodologies</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                            <div class="col-md-6">
                                <h5>Course Features:</h5>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>10 comprehensive modules</li>
                                    <li>Downloadable PDF presentations</li>
                                    <li>Practical examples and exercises</li>
                                    <li>Final capstone project</li>
                                    <li>Progressive difficulty levels</li>
                                    <li>Real-world applications</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </main>

    <footer class="bg-dark text-light text-center py-3 mt-5">
        <p>&copy; 2025 JavaScript Learning Platform. All rights reserved.</p>
    </footer>

    <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.1.3/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>
    <script src="/js/main.js"></script>
</body>
</html>